Now login to node and enable HTTP Access logs
•	Open command prompt / terminal
•	Locate server.xml
Example paths:
Linux: /opt/atlassian/jira/conf/server.xml 
Windows: C:\Atlassian\Jira\conf\server.xml
•	Sudo nano server.xml
•	Now add or uncomment the following:
<Valve className="org.apache.catalina.valves.AccessLogValve"
       directory="logs"
       prefix="jira_access_log"
       suffix=".log"
       pattern="%h %l %u %t &quot;%r&quot; %s %b"
       resolveHosts="false" />
•	For better security auditing use this enhanced pattern
pattern="%h %l %u %t &quot;%r&quot; %s %b %{User-Agent}i"
•	Now to save press ctrl + O and to exit ctrl + X
•	Now restart the node using below command
  <JIRA_INSTALL>/bin/stop-jira.sh
  <JIRA_INSTALL>/bin/start-jira.sh
•	Now the access log will be written to: 
  <JIRA_INSTALL>/logs/jira_access_log.YYYY-MM-DD.log
•	Just verify the file logging is working or not (Audit proof)
  ls -lh <JIRA_INSTALL>/logs/jira_access_log*
•	You have to follow these steps on each node.
•	Now just open jira in a browser and login
•	Browse some issue
•	Now these information will be present in the access log
